Class PrometheusController

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.ps51.utility.Observable<EventForClient>
it.polimi.ingsw.ps51.utility.GodControllerObservable
it.polimi.ingsw.ps51.controller.gods.NormalGodsController
it.polimi.ingsw.ps51.controller.gods.PrometheusController
All Implemented Interfaces:
GodController, GodControllerWithDecision
public class PrometheusController
extends NormalGodsController
implements GodControllerWithDecision
This class implements the logic to manage a turn done by a player who have the Prometheus god. The player can build also before moving if and only if when he will move his worker he don't moves it up

  • Method Details

    • searchForMoves

      public void searchForMoves()
      The method retrieves the list of the coordinates where the worker can be moved and send a ChooseMove event to the player with this list. If the power of the god is used, before sending the list to the player the coordinates that impose to the worker to moves up are removed from the list and set back the attribute useGodPower to false
      Overrides:
      searchForMoves in class NormalGodsController

    • preBuild

      protected void preBuild​(Coordinates buildOn, Level level)
      The method implements the build action when this one is done before moving the player, it's similar to the standard build except for the fact that at the end of it the turn doesn't end, but the method searchForMoves() will be called
      Parameters:
      buildOn - the coordinates where the new level must be built
      level - the level that must be built

    • manageWorkerChoice

      public void manageWorkerChoice​(Worker worker)
      The method is called as a consequence of receiving a WorkerChoice event that specifies which of the player's workers must be selected to perform the turn. Then check if the worker can be moved without moving it up, if it's possible, send to the player a MakeDecision event to ask him if wants to use or not the god's power
      Specified by:
      manageWorkerChoice in interface GodController
      Overrides:
      manageWorkerChoice in class NormalGodsController
      Parameters:
      worker - the selected worker

    • decisionManager

      public void decisionManager​(boolean takenDecision)
      The method is called as a consequence of receiving a DecisionTaken event, the decision is about building before moving or not
      Specified by:
      decisionManager in interface GodControllerWithDecision
      Parameters:
      takenDecision - is true if the player want to build before moving, false if the player want to play a classical turn
